-> Initialize the Git repository
     git init
-> Create a .gitignore to ignore node_modules and large/OS-specific files
-> Create a .gitattributes for consistent line endings
-> Stage project files (excluding node_modules)
     git add index.html main.js photo.jpg package.json package-lock.json .gitignore .gitattributes

-> Commit the clean project
     git commit -m "Initial commit - clean VR Electron project"

-> Add GitHub remote (replace with your URL)
    git remote add origin https://github.com/manasadhandu/electron-js-html-vr.git

-> Set the main branch
    git branch -M main

->Push project to GitHub
   git push -u origin main
 
  Electron / NPM Commands
️-> Install dependencies locally
     npm install
     This creates the node_modules folder locally. Do not commit this to GitHub.
️-> Run the Electron app
     npm start
-> Install Node.js & NPM (if not installed)
     Check if Node.js is installed:
     node -v
    npm -v

-> Create Electron Project
    mkdir my-electron-app
    cd my-electron-app
    npm init -y
    npm install electron --save-dev

-> Test Electron:
    npx electron --version

-> Run Electron App
    npm start
    npx electron .

-> Install & Run HTTP Server
    Install once globally:
    npm install -g http-server

-> Run HTTP server on port 61775:
    http-server -p 61775
  
-> You’ll see output like:
    Available on:
    http://192.168.1.6:61775
    http://127.0.0.1:61775

-> Use the 192.168.x.x address on Meta Quest 3 (local network).

-> Install Local SSL Proxy (for HTTPS)
   Install:
   npm install -g local-ssl-proxy

-> Run proxy (maps HTTPS → HTTP):
   npx local-ssl-proxy --source 3443 --target 61775
This creates:
https://localhost:3443 → http://localhost:61775

-> Kill Port if Already Used
   Check if port 3443 is busy:
   netstat -ano | findstr :3443

-> Find the PID and stop it:
   tasklist /FI "PID eq <PID>"
   taskkill /PID <PID> /F

Example:
  taskkill /PID 13588 /F

